getSimThreshold

public double getSimThreshold()
Default 0. Limits the output generated from the simulation to only save points which delta tau > threshold. Can greatly reduce the required memory!

setSimThreshold

public void setSimThreshold(double threshold)
See getOutputStepCount().

getSimRateMode

public int getSimRateMode()
How the algorithms should calculate rates. Currently two modes are supported:
  • Constant rate (PARAM_SIM_RATE_MODE_CONSTANT): The rate is constant, and the reactants of a reaction is parsed to the binomial function, ensuring that the rate will change depending on the amount of available reactants.
  • Custom function rate (PARAM_SIM_RATE_MODE_CUSTOM): A valid mathematical expression representing the rate of a reaction. This will typically depend on one or more species in the system.

See getSimRateMode().

getCustom

public java.lang.String getCustom(java.lang.String key,
                                  java.lang.String value)
If the parameter don't have a static field in this class, the parameter can be retrieved with this method. This should mainly be used in custom implementations of parsers, algorithms, etc.

Parameters:
key - The parameter.
value - The default value if the parameter is not present.
Returns:
The value of the parameter.
